CSI/ATSI Designations

Under ESSA, schools can be identified for Comprehensive Support and Improvement (CSI) or Additional Targeted Support and Improvement (ATSI). CSI is based on a schoolâs overall or All Students indicators, whereas ATSI is based on each student groupâs indicators. For more information please see: CDE School Support. It is important to note that calculations are only based on student groups with 30 or more students.

Robert Down Elementary is eligible for ATSI.

Status Needed to Avoid Red in 2024

This section estimates the limits for indicators to receive an orange or higher color next year on the 2024 Dashboard. The thresholds below are based on the 5x5 grids last approved by the State Board of Education and the number of students in the 2023 calculation. State policies may change and the student counts may shift. Only student groups in DA and their qualifying indicators for Pacific Grove Unified are included below and only if they are in the lowest status for Robert Down Elementary. The thresholds represent the numbers for Robert Down Elementary.
